,Recommended,312280,29684918,Posted: 3 February,all,Jaeger,"Simply Charming!Its all the in title of the game really, thats what you are getting. not poker, not ludo, not bloody go fish But a respectable and sophisticated game that has been adapted and reformatted for over 1000 years..When you have played for as long as i have, its quite a complex game. one with many things to learn when you start playing for more than 2 hours (Most people dont arent very devoted, which is ok since there is a learning cap in this game anyway.) Although once you have learnt everything its up to the original structure of the game itself to keep you interested!I grew up playing chess, so it was just a matter of time untill i played this.Pretty much does what it says in the description, nothing more, nothing less. And i love it for that.Its no skyrim or cs go but its a very relaxing Board game for the more patient of the steam players. :)If chess itself doesnt interest you then obviously dont get this, but if you like challenging board games where you have much control over the difficulty and style then try this!oh yeah..and its free (Although consider buying the premium edition if you have played over 10 hours ;)Nothing is more satisying then taking out all the opponents pieces except the king..-Kyle"
